00:07:16.720 --> 00:07:20.960
 input voltage is increased. You want a smooth transition for your output voltage. You want the

00:07:20.960 --> 00:07:24.880
 output voltage to be higher but you also want it to be smooth because you're trying to do an

00:07:24.880 --> 00:07:33.040
 amplification and so the right curve has a nice sort of 45 degree angle linear sloped amplification.

00:07:33.760 --> 00:07:40.000
 The problem is that when you have such a long time before it kind of goes from the low voltage to the

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:46.720
 high voltage that makes the transition period too long. So there's a voltage range that's a zero,

00:07:46.720 --> 00:07:50.960
 there's a voltage range that's transition, and then there's a voltage range that is one.

